<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <title>TransitCloud — Verifiable Documents (Developer Edition)</title>
  <meta name="description" content="TransitCloud converts financial documents into cryptographically verifiable instruments: deterministic canonicalization, SHA-256 root hashes, Ed25519 signatures, proof bundles, and optional on-chain anchoring." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="topbar">
    <div class="container topbar__inner">
      <a class="brand" href="./index.html">
        <span class="brand__mark" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="brand__name">TransitCloud</span>
        <span class="brand__tag">Developer Edition</span>
      </a>

      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="./docs.html">Docs</a>
        <a href="./developers.html">Developers</a>
        <a href="#security">Security</a>
        <a href="#pilot">Pilot</a>
      </nav>

      <div class="topbar__cta">
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="./docs.html#quickstart">Quickstart</a>
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href="#contact">Request a Pilot</a>
        <button class="iconbtn" id="themeToggle" aria-label="Toggle theme" title="Toggle theme">◐</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero__grid">
        <div class="hero__copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Verifiable Financial Documents • Proof Bundles • Optional Onchain Anchors</p>
          <h1>Documents that verify themselves.</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            TransitCloud turns invoices, receipts, and audit records into tamper-evident instruments:
            deterministic canonicalization, SHA-256 root hashes, Ed25519 signatures, and portable proof bundles.
          </p>

          <div class="hero__actions">
            <a class="btn btn--primary" href="./docs.html#quickstart">Start building</a>
            <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="./developers.html#api">View API</a>
          </div>

          <div class="hero__meta">
            <div class="metaCard">
              <div class="metaCard__k">Integrity</div>
              <div class="metaCard__v">SHA-256 root hash</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metaCard">
              <div class="metaCard__k">Authenticity</div>
              <div class="metaCard__v">Ed25519 signatures</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metaCard">
              <div class="metaCard__k">Reproducibility</div>
              <div class="metaCard__v">Canonical JSON</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero__panel">
          <div class="terminal">
            <div class="terminal__bar">
              <span class="dot dot--r"></span><span class="dot dot--y"></span><span class="dot dot--g"></span>
              <span class="terminal__title">verify-doc.sh</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="terminal__body"><code>$ transitcloud canonize invoice.json > invoice.canonical.json
$ transitcloud hash invoice.canonical.json
sha256: e5fc9f810e6297def781caca7041ae1bdf8bf6175c1c2e2b759f9ea1caddea90

$ transitcloud sign --key ed25519_private.pem invoice.canonical.json > invoice.sig
$ transitcloud verify --pub ed25519_public.pem --sig invoice.sig invoice.canonical.json
OK: signature valid

$ transitcloud bundle invoice.canonical.json invoice.sig > proof.bundle.json
OK: proof bundle created</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="panelNote">
            Built for regulated workflows: audit trails, receipts, custody, and provable document movement.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="value">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section__head">
          <h2>Why TransitCloud</h2>
          <p>Stop relying on “trust me” documents. Make verification native to the document itself.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid3">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Deterministic builds</h3>
            <p>Canonical JSON pipelines produce reproducible outputs and stable hashes across environments.</p>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>Canonicalization rules</li>
              <li>Strict field ordering</li>
              <li>Stable hashing inputs</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="card">
            <h3>Portable proof bundles</h3>
            <p>Ship the proof with the document. Verify offline. Store long-term. Audit later.</p>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>Root hash + metadata</li>
              <li>Signature sets</li>
              <li>Receipts & custody events</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="card">
            <h3>Onchain-ready anchors</h3>
            <p>Optionally anchor roots on EVM networks for public timestamped attestation.</p>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>Hash → chain anchor</li>
              <li>Proof-of-record</li>
              <li>Non-custodial verification</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--alt" id="security">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="split">
          <div>
            <h2>Security model</h2>
            <p class="lead2">
              TransitCloud is designed for integrity, authenticity, and traceability.
              The system does not depend on a central database for verification.
            </p>
            <div class="miniGrid">
              <div class="miniCard">
                <div class="miniCard__title">Threat: document tampering</div>
                <div class="miniCard__desc">Mitigation: canonicalization + content hash; any change breaks verification.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="miniCard">
                <div class="miniCard__title">Threat: forged issuer</div>
                <div class="miniCard__desc">Mitigation: Ed25519 signatures + key fingerprint pinning.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="miniCard">
                <div class="miniCard__title">Threat: audit disputes</div>
                <div class="miniCard__desc">Mitigation: proof bundle includes receipts, roots, and custody events.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card card--code">
            <h3>Verification primitives</h3>
            <pre><code>Canonical JSON  → stable bytes
SHA-256         → deterministic root hash
Ed25519         → issuer authenticity
Bundle          → portable proof record
Anchor (opt.)   → public timestamp attestation</code></pre>
            <a class="link" href="./developers.html#recipes">See verification recipes →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="pilot">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="callout">
          <div class="callout__copy">
            <h2>South Carolina pilot-ready</h2>
            <p>
              TransitCloud can be piloted with invoices, receipts, and audit records under strict controls:
              limited participants, clear disclosures, and full logging.
            </p>
            <div class="callout__badges">
              <span class="badge">No speculative trading</span>
              <span class="badge">Audit-first</span>
              <span class="badge">Compliance friendly</span>
              <span class="badge">Offline verifiable</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="callout__cta">
            <a class="btn btn--primary" href="#contact">Request a pilot</a>
            <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="./docs.html#sandbox">Sandbox packet</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="contact">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section__head">
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>Use this form to generate a ready-to-send email template. It copies to your clipboard.</p>
        </div>

        <form class="form" id="contactForm">
          <div class="formRow">
            <label>
              Recipient (optional)
              <input type="text" id="recipient" placeholder="Securities Division / Innovation Contact" />
            </label>
            <label>
              Your email
              <input type="email" id="fromEmail" placeholder="kam@domain.com" />
            </label>
          </div>

          <label>
            Message focus
            <select id="focus">
              <option value="sandbox">Sandbox / innovation review</option>
              <option value="pilot">Business pilot</option>
              <option value="enterprise">Enterprise verification</option>
            </select>
          </label>

          <label>
            Notes (optional)
            <textarea id="notes" rows="4" placeholder="Any details you want included…"></textarea>
          </label>

          <div class="formActions">
            <button class="btn btn--primary" type="submit">Generate email</button>
            <button class="btn btn--ghost" type="button" id="copyEmailBtn" disabled>Copy</button>
          </div>

          <div class="output" id="emailOutput" aria-live="polite"></div>
        </form>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container footer__grid">
      <div>
        <div class="footer__brand">TransitCloud</div>
        <div class="footer__sub">Verifiable document infrastructure for finance and audit.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="footer__links">
        <a href="./docs.html">Docs</a>
        <a href="./developers.html">Developers</a>
        <a href="./docs.html#spec">Spec</a>
        <a href="./developers.html#api">API</a>
      </div>
      <div class="footer__meta">
        <div>© <span id="year"></span> Kam Swygert</div>
        <div class="muted">Developer Edition</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script src="./app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
